    "Despite these advancements, the significant variation in success rates indicates that outdoor VLN systems must address the challenges of diverse environmental conditions and dynamic elements more effectively to achieve reliable performance in real-world applications (Challenge 6.3).",
    "Apart from VLN in real-world environments, Chen et al. (2024) proposed a VLN model for web environments.",
    "They utilized GPT-3.5 and BLIP-2 to construct a WebVLN model capable of answering questions based on web content and automatically navigating to the required web pages.",
    "They also created a WebVLN-v1 data set, where the WebVLN model achieved a task completion rate of 34.7%.",
    "This is a newly proposed task that has not yet been explored in the industrial sector, but it has potential applications in industrial QA systems."
